Introduced Version
HOUSE
RESOLUTION No. ___
Introduced by: Smith V, Harris, Jackson C, Bartlett, Burton,
Hatcher, Pack, Porter, Pryor, Shackleford, Summers
____________________________________
1 A HOUSE RESOLUTION commemorating Dr. Martin
2 Luther King Jr. Day.
3 Whereas, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. was one of our nation's
4 truly great leaders;
5 Whereas, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. changed our nation
6 forever through his leadership, service, and clarity of vision;
7 Whereas, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. had many dreams: of
8 an America where "justice rolls down like waters and
9 righteousness like a mighty stream"; where neighbors look
10 "beyond the external accidents and discern those inner qualities
11 that make all men human and, therefore, brothers"; and of a
12 time when "this nation will rise up and live out the true
13 meaning of its creed: 'We hold these truths to be self-evident:
20262331
HR 1506/DI 140 2026

2
1 that all men are created equal.'";
2 Whereas, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. dreamt of a better
3 society where "the sons of former slaves and the sons of former
4 slave owners will be able to sit down together at the table of
5 brotherhood";
6 Whereas, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. believed that liberty,
7 justice, and freedom were the "inalienable rights" to which all
8 men, women, and children are entitled;
9 Whereas, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. was a spiritual man
10 who believed that all people are created equal in the sight of
11 God and in the dignity and self-worth of every individual;
12 Whereas, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. gave his life defending
13 his beliefs;
14 Whereas, The visions of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. continue
15 to bring hope and inspiration to people of all nations;
16 Whereas, Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., a recipient of the
17 Nobel Peace Prize, is a national hero whose birthday is
18 celebrated as a day of peace, love, and understanding by a
19 grateful nation in the form of a national holiday, as well as a
20 state holiday in Indiana; and
21 Whereas, All Americans must continue to gather inspiration
22 from the life of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. and strive to realize
23 his dreams: Therefore,
24 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the
25 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
26 SECTION 1. That it is fitting and proper that Dr. Martin
27 Luther King Jr. be remembered and recognized by future
28 generations of Americans and that all citizens of Indiana honor
29 Dr. King by living out his teachings as we continue to work
30 toward a day when the dignity and humanity of every person are
31 respected.
32 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
33 Representatives transmit a copy of this resolution to the family
